President Donald J. Trump has declared an emergency in Puerto Rico due to the conditions caused by Tropical Storm Laura. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts to alleviate the suffering of the local population and provide necessary assistance. FEMA is authorized to identify, mobilize, and provide equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The assistance will include mass care, evacuation, and shelter support, with 75 percent of the funding coming from the federal government. Alexis Amparo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.